100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 3, 1926, British Prime Minister Stanley Baldwin announced a new legislative agenda aimed at economic recovery following the post-war slump. Meanwhile, in the United States, the ongoing debate over Prohibition intensified as several states pushed for repeal measures. In Europe, tensions remained high as Germany grappled with reparations payments, while Italy's Mussolini continued to consolidate power.
